MEDICAL RECORDS & RECOMMENDATIONS:
--------------------------------------------------
Employee: Jean Du Plessis
Report Date: 2021-03-09
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Clinically you examine well with a good BMI. A marginally increased body fat % can be reduced with exercise. If any concerning skin lesions arise, we recommend mole mapping screening with a Dermatologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: Regular prostate screening is important to detect any irregularities early. You report no current concerning symptoms and your blood PSA levels (screening marker) were normal.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Raised homocysteine - is also a risk factor for heart disease. To reduce your homocysteine levels supplement with active B vitamins such as those found in metagenics phytomulti or methylcare or homocysteine lowering formula from solal. Aim for an optimal level around 8
Comment Key: ChronicMedicationList
Comment Value: Lorien 20mg , Ezetimibe , Rosuvastatin
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Comment Value: Lorien 20mg , Ezetimibe , Rosuvastatin
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: Regular prostate screening is important to detect any irregularities early. You report no current concerning symptoms and your blood PSA levels (screening marker) were normal.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Slightly raised uric acid - watch red meat in your diet and alcohol consumption
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Clinical Recommendations: Clinically you examine well with a good BMI. A marginally increased body fat % can be reduced with exercise. If any concerning skin lesions arise, we recommend mole mapping screening with a Dermatologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: Please report any new worrying or persistent urinary symptoms to your doctor.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Raised cholesterol and triglycerides - restart taking your cholesterol medication, maintain a healthy, low sugar diet and continue with your new exercise regime.

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Raised homocysteine - is also a risk factor for heart disease. To reduce your homocysteine levels supplement with active B vitamins such as those found in metagenics phytomulti or methylcare or homocysteine lowering formula from solal. Aim for an optimal level around 8

Men's Health Recommendations: Regular prostate screening is important to detect any irregularities early. You report no current concerning symptoms and your blood PSA levels (screening marker) were normal.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Slightly raised urea on kidney functions suggestive of dehydration. Ensure you are drinking enough water throughout the day.
Comment Key: CurrentComplaintRecommendation

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations:

Women's Health Recommendations:

Men's Health Recommendations: Please report any new worrying or persistent urinary symptoms to your doctor.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Raised homocysteine - is also a risk factor for heart disease. To reduce your homocysteine levels supplement with active B vitamins such as those found in metagenics phytomulti or methylcare or homocysteine lowering formula from solal. Aim for an optimal level around 8
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryRecommendation
Comment Value: You are taking all the necessary steps to manage your chronic conditions. Keep choosing a healthy lifestyle to reduce the need for further medications.

Overview Notes: Raised cholesterol and triglycerides - restart taking your cholesterol medication, maintain a healthy, low sugar diet and continue with your new exercise regime.

Men's Health Recommendations: Regular prostate screening is important to detect any irregularities early. You report no current concerning symptoms and your blood PSA levels (screening marker) were normal.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol, Family History, Age and Male, one episode of atrial fibrillation but normal angiogram
Comment Key: MentalHealthMoodRecommendation
Comment Value: None

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Clinically you examine well with a good BMI. A marginally increased body fat % can be reduced with exercise. If any concerning skin lesions arise, we recommend mole mapping screening with a Dermatologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: Regular prostate screening is important to detect any irregularities early. You report no current concerning symptoms and your blood PSA levels (screening marker) were normal.

Overview Notes: Raised homocysteine - is also a risk factor for heart disease. To reduce your homocysteine levels supplement with active B vitamins such as those found in metagenics phytomulti or methylcare or homocysteine lowering formula from solal. Aim for an optimal level around 8
Comment Key: SpecialInvestigationNote
Comment Value: Nil
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Clinical Recommendations: Clinically you examine well with a good BMI. A marginally increased body fat % can be reduced with exercise. If any concerning skin lesions arise, we recommend mole mapping screening with a Dermatologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: Please report any new worrying or persistent urinary symptoms to your doctor.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Started exercising again
Healthy diet
Non smoker
Low levels of inflammation indicated by hsCRP level

Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Clinically you examine well with a good BMI. A marginally increased body fat % can be reduced with exercise. If any concerning skin lesions arise, we recommend mole mapping screening with a Dermatologist.
Men's Health Recommendations: Regular prostate screening is important to detect any irregularities early. You report no current concerning symptoms and your blood PSA levels (screening marker) were normal.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: 0
